-- Asahi Glass Plans to Buy Out Rest of South Korea's Hankuk Electric Glass
-- B y   T a k   K u m a k u r a
-- 2010-10-07T00:17:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/asahi-glass-plans-to-buy-out-rest-of-south-korea-s-hankuk-electric-glass.html
Asahi Glass Co. will buy out Hankuk
Electric Glass Co. for 55,000 won a share, making the South
Korean company a wholly owned unit. Asahi Glass made the
announcement today in a press release. Asahi Glass now owns 51
percent of Hankuk Electric Glass.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Takehiko Kumakura at 
 tkumakura@bloomberg.net  